    "engine": "knitr",
    "markdown": "---\ntitle: \"Code\"\nsubtitle: \"Some code from my Environmental Statistics class.\"\nauthor: \"Claire Timm\"\ndate: \"2026-03-11\"\ncategories: [coding]\nimage: \"images.jpeg\"\ntheme: materia\n---\n\nThis is a sample of code from my personal data project for my Environmental Statistics class. I centered my project around the research question \"Does my screen time usage in the day affect my sleep duration that night?\". Additionally I tracked other predictor variables such as step count, time spent on schoolwork, exercise duration, and caffeine intake. \n\n## Set up\n\n\n::: {.cell}\n\n```{.r .cell-code}\n#read in packages here\nlibrary(tidyverse)\nlibrary(plotly) \nlibrary(DT) \nlibrary(leaflet) \nlibrary(here)\nlibrary(janitor)\nlibrary(readxl)\nlibrary(ggeffects)\nlibrary(readr)\n\n#read in data here\nmy_data <- read_csv(here::here(\"posts\", \"code\", \"mydata.csv\"))\n```\n:::\n\n\n## Clean up data\n\n\n::: {.cell}\n\n```{.r .cell-code}\nmy_data_clean <- my_data |> #create new object for cleaned personal data\n  rename(date = \"Date (mm/dd/yyyy)\", #renames column 'date'\n         day = \"Day of Week\", #renames colum 'day'\n         sleep_duration = \"Sleep Duration (minutes)\", #renames column 'sleep_duration'\n         step_count = \"Step Count\", #renames colum 'step_count'\n         homework_duration = \"Time spent on homework (minutes)\", #renames column 'homework_duration'\n         screen_time = \"Screen Time (minutes)\", #renames column 'screen_time'\n         exercise_duration = \"Exercise duration (minutes)\", #renames_column 'exercise_duration'\n         caffeine_intake = \"Caffeine Intake (mg)\") #renames column 'caffeine_intake' \n```\n:::\n\n\n## Graph with a continuous predictor:\n\n\n::: {.cell}\n\n```{.r .cell-code}\n#base layer: ggplot call \nggplot(data = my_data_clean, #start with data frame 'my_data_clean'\n       aes(x = screen_time, #x-axis is data of 'screen_time'\n           y = sleep_duration)) + #y-axis is data of 'sleep_duration'\n  geom_point(color = \"purple4\", shape = 18, size = 3, na.rm = TRUE) + #changes the point color, shape, and size \n  labs(x = \"Screen Time (minutes)\", #adds x-axis title\n       y = \"Sleep Duration (minutes)\", #adds y-axis title \n       title = \"How Screen Time affects Sleep Duration\", #adds a graph title \n       subtitle = \"Most recent observation: 03/11/2026\") + #adds a graph subtitle \n  theme_minimal() #changes graph theme \n```\n\n::: {.cell-output-display}\n![](index_files/figure-html/graph of my data with continuous predictor-1.png){width=672}\n:::\n:::\n\n\n**Figure 1. Relationship between daily screen time (minutes) and sleep duration (minutes).** The scatter plot graphs the relationship between daily screen time and sleep duration that night in minutes. Each purple diamond represents an observation. Screen time is on the x-axis in minutes and sleep duration is on the y-axis in minutes. The data shows the variation in sleep duration across different levels of screen time.\n\n## Graph with a categorical predictor:\n\n\n::: {.cell}\n\n```{.r .cell-code}\norder <- c(\"Monday\", \"Tuesday\", \"Wednesday\", \"Thursday\", \"Friday\") #defines the order of weekdays\nstatic <- my_data_clean |> \nggplot(aes(x = factor(day, level = order), #x-axis should be day of the week but converted in order of weekday \n           y = sleep_duration, #y-axis should be sleep duration in minutes\n           fill = factor(day, level = order))) + #fills in the boxes by day of week\n  geom_boxplot(na.rm = TRUE) + #first layer is a boxplot and removes NA values\n  geom_jitter(aes(text = paste(\n    \"Day:\", day,\n    \"<br>Sleep Duration:\", sleep_duration, \"minutes\"\n  )),\n  width = 0.2, #makes the points jitter horizontally \n  height = 0,  #makes the points not jitter horizontally \n  na.rm = TRUE) + #removes NA values \n         labs(x = \"Day of Week\", #adds x-axis title\n              y = \"Sleep Duration (minutes)\", #adds y-axis title \n              title = \"Distribution of Sleep Duration by Day of the Week\", #adds graph title\n              subtitle = \"Most recent observation: 03/11/2026\", #adds a graph subtitle\n              fill = \"Day of Week\") + #adds legend title \n  scale_fill_manual(values = c( #changes the color of each group\n      \"Monday\" = \"lightgoldenrod\", #changes Monday data color\n      \"Tuesday\" = \"lightpink2\",  #changes Tuesday data color\n      \"Wednesday\" = \"lightsalmon3\", #changes Wednesday data color\n      \"Thursday\" = \"lightskyblue3\", #changes Thurday data color \n      \"Friday\" = \"mediumorchid4\")) + #changes Friday data color \n  theme_minimal() + #changes theme of graph \n  theme(legend.position = \"none\") #removes legend\n#show interactive plot\nggplotly(static, tooltip = \"text\") \n```\n\n::: {.cell-output-display}\n\n```{=html}\n<div class=\"plotly html-widget html-fill-item\" id=\"htmlwidget-e984c6851cf79a75e055\" style=\"width:100%;height:464px;\"></div>\n<script type=\"application/json\" data-for=\"htmlwidget-e984c6851cf79a75e055\">{\"x\":{\"data\":[{\"x\":[1,1,1,1,1,1,1],\"y\":[437,474,440,647,502,410,477],\"hoverinfo\":\"y\",\"type\":\"box\",\"fillcolor\":\"rgba(238,221,130,1)\",\"marker\":{\"opacity\":null,\"outliercolor\":\"rgba(0,0,0,1)\",\"line\":{\"width\":1.8897637795275593,\"color\":\"rgba(0,0,0,1)\"},\"size\":5.6692913385826778},\"line\":{\"color\":\"rgba(51,51,51,1)\",\"width\":1.8897637795275593},\"name\":\"Monday\",\"legendgroup\":\"Monday\",\"showlegend\":true,\"xaxis\":\"x\",\"yaxis\":\"y\",\"frame\":null},{\"x\":[2,2,2,2,2,2,2],\"y\":[382,387,402,362,523,372,427],\"hoverinfo\":\"y\",\"type\":\"box\",\"fillcolor\":\"rgba(238,162,173,1)\",\"marker\":{\"opacity\":null,\"outliercolor\":\"rgba(0,0,0,1)\",\"line\":{\"width\":1.8897637795275593,\"color\":\"rgba(0,0,0,1)\"},\"size\":5.6692913385826778},\"line\":{\"color\":\"rgba(51,51,51,1)\",\"width\":1.8897637795275593},\"name\":\"Tuesday\",\"legendgroup\":\"Tuesday\",\"showlegend\